bit_field.name: ETMPD
bit_field.description: ETM power down. This bit can be used by an implementation to control if the ETM is in a low power state. This bit must be cleared by the trace software tools at the beginning of a debug session. When this bit is set to 1, writes to some registers and fields might be ignored.

bit_field.name: PS
bit_field.description: Port size. The ETM-M4 has no influence over the external pins used for trace. These bits are implemented but not used. On an ETM reset these bits reset to 0b001.

bit_field.name: SP
bit_field.description: Stall processor. The FIFOFULL output can be used to stall the processor to prevent overflow. The FIFOFULL output is only enabled when the stall processor bit is set to 1. When the bit is 0 the FIFOFULL output remains LOW at all times and the FIFO overflows if there are too many trace packets. Trace resumes without corruption once the FIFO has drained, if overflow does occur. An ETM reset sets this bit to 0.

bit_field.name: BO
bit_field.description: Branch output. When set to 1 all branch addresses are output, even if the branch was because of a direct branch instruction. Setting this bit enables reconstruction of the program flow without having access to the memory image of the code being executed. When this bit is set to 1, more trace data is generated, and this may affect the performance of the trace system. Information about the execution of a branch is traced regardless of the state of this bit. An ETM reset sets this bit to 0.

bit_field.name: DRC
bit_field.description: Debug request control. When set to 1 and the trigger event occurs, the DBGRQ output is asserted until DBGACK is observed. This enables the ARM processor to be forced into Debug state. An ETM reset sets this bit to 0.

bit_field.name: ETMP
bit_field.description: ETM programming. This bit must be set to 1 at the start of the ETM programming sequence. Tracing is prevented while this bit is set to 1. On an ETM reset this bit is set to b1.

bit_field.name: ETMPS
bit_field.description: ETM port selection. This bit can be used to control other trace components in an implementation. This bit must be set by the trace software tools to ensure that trace output is enabled from this ETM. An ETM reset sets this bit to 0.

bit_field.name: PM2
bit_field.description: This bit is implemented but has no function. An ETM reset sets this bit to 0.

bit_field.name: PM
bit_field.description: These bits are implemented but have no function. An ETM reset sets these bits to 0.

bit_field.name: PS3
bit_field.description: This bit is implemented but has no function. An ETM reset sets this bit to 0.

bit_field.name: TE
bit_field.description: When set, this bit enables timestamping. An ETM reset sets this bit to 0.

bit_field.name: NumberOfAddressComparatorPairs
bit_field.description: Number of address comparator pairs. The value of these bits is b0000, indicating that address comparator pairs are not implemented.

bit_field.name: NDVC
bit_field.description: Number of data value comparators. The value of these bits is b0000, indicating that data value comparators are not implemented.

bit_field.name: NMMD
bit_field.description: Number of memory map decoders. The value of these bits is b00000, indicating that memory map decoder inputs are not implemented.

bit_field.name: NC
bit_field.description: Number of counters. The value of these bits is b001, indicating that one counter is implemented.

bit_field.name: SP
bit_field.description: Sequencer present. The value of this bit is 0, indicating that the sequencer is not implemented.

bit_field.name: NEI
bit_field.description: Number of external inputs. The value of these bits is between b000 and b010, indicating the number of external inputs, from 0 to 2, implemented in the system.

bit_field.name: NEO
bit_field.description: Number of external outputs. The value of these bits is b000, indicating that no external outputs are supported.

bit_field.name: FFLP
bit_field.description: FIFOFULL logic present. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that FIFOFULL logic is present in the ETM. To use FIFOFULL the system must also support the function, as indicated by bit [8] of ETMSCR.

bit_field.name: NCIDC
bit_field.description: Number of Context ID comparators. The value of these bits is b00, indicating that Context ID comparators are not implemented.

bit_field.name: TSSBP
bit_field.description: Trace start/stop block present. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that the Trace start/stop block is present.

bit_field.name: CMA
bit_field.description: Coprocessor and memory access. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that memory-mapped access to registers is supported.

bit_field.name: ETMIDRP
bit_field.description: The value of this bit is 1, indicating that the ETMIDR, register 0x79, is present and defines the ETM architecture version in use.

bit_field.name: TriggerEvent
bit_field.description: Trigger event

bit_field.name: UOF
bit_field.description: Untraced overflow flag. If set to 1, there is an overflow that has not yet been traced. This bit is cleared to 0 when either: - trace is restarted - the ETM Power Down bit, bit [0] of the ETM Control Register, 0x00, is set to 1. Note: Setting or clearing the ETM programming bit does not cause this bit to be cleared to 0.

bit_field.name: Progbit
bit_field.description: ETM programming bit value (Progbit). The current effective value of the ETM Programming bit (ETM Control Register bit [10]). Tou must wait for this bit to go to 1 before you start to program the ETM.

bit_field.name: Status
bit_field.description: Holds the current status of the trace start/stop resource. If set to 1, it indicates that a trace on address has been matched, without a corresponding trace off address match.

bit_field.name: Trigger
bit_field.description: Trigger bit. Set when the trigger occurs, and prevents the trigger from being output until the ETM is next programmed.

bit_field.name: MaximumPortSize
bit_field.description: Maximum ETM port size bits [2:0]. These bits are used in conjunction with bit [9]. The value of these bits is b001.

bit_field.name: FIFOFULLsupported
bit_field.description: FIFOFULL supported. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that FIFOFULL is supported. This bit is used in conjunction with bit [23] of the ETMCCR.

bit_field.name: MaximumPortSize3
bit_field.description: Maximum ETM port size bit [3]. This bit is used in conjunction with bits [2:0]. Its value is 0. This has no effect on the TPIU trace port.

bit_field.name: PortSizeSupported
bit_field.description: Port size supported. This bit reads as 1 if the currently selected port size is supported. This has no effect on the TPIU trace port.

bit_field.name: PortModeSupported
bit_field.description: Port mode supported. This bit reads as 1 if the currently selected port mode is supported. This has no effect on the TPIU trace port.

bit_field.name: N
bit_field.description: These bits give the number of supported processors minus 1. The value of these bits is b000, indicating that there is only one processor connected.

bit_field.name: NoFetchComparisons
bit_field.description: No Fetch comparisons. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that fetch comparisons are not implemented.

bit_field.name: TraceEnableEvent
bit_field.description: Trace Enable event.

bit_field.name: TraceControlEnable
bit_field.description: Trace start/stop enable. The trace start/stop resource, resource 0x5F, is unaffected by the value of this bit.

bit_field_value.name: ETMTECR1_TraceControlEnable_0b0
bit_field_value.description: Tracing is unaffected by the trace start/stop logic.

bit_field_value.name: ETMTECR1_TraceControlEnable_0b1
bit_field_value.description: Tracing is controlled by the trace on and off addresses configured for the trace start/stop logic.

bit_field.name: FIFOFullLevel
bit_field.description: FIFO full level. The number of bytes left in FIFO, below which the FIFOFULL or SupressData signal is asserted. For example, setting this value to 15 causes data trace suppression or processor stalling, if enabled, when there are less than 15 free bytes in the FIFO.

bit_field.name: IntitialCount
bit_field.description: Initial count.

bit_field.name: SyncFrequency
bit_field.description: Synchronization frequency. Default value is 1024.

bit_field.name: ImplementationRevision
bit_field.description: Implementation revision. The value of these bits is b0000, indicating implementation revision, 0.

bit_field.name: MinorETMarchitectureVersion
bit_field.description: Minor ETM architecture version. The value of these bits is 0b0101, indicating minor architecture version number 5.

bit_field.name: MajorETMarchitectureVersion
bit_field.description: Major ETM architecture version. The value of these bits is 0b0010, indicating major architecture version number 3, ETMv3.

bit_field.name: ProcessorFamily
bit_field.description: Processor family. The value of these bits is 0b1111, indicating that the processor family is not identified in this register.

bit_field.name: LoadPCfirst
bit_field.description: Load PC first. The value of this bit is 0, indicating that data tracing is not supported.

bit_field.name: ThumbInstructionTracing
bit_field.description: 32-bit Thumb instruction tracing. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that a 32-bit Thumb instruction is traced as a single instruction.

bit_field_value.name: ETMIDR_ThumbInstructionTracing_0b0
bit_field_value.description: A 32-bit Thumb instruction is traced as two instructions, and exceptions might occur between these two instructions.

bit_field_value.name: ETMIDR_ThumbInstructionTracing_0b1
bit_field_value.description: A 32-bit Thimb instruction is traced as a single instruction.

bit_field.name: SecurityExtensionSupport
bit_field.description: Security Extensions support. The value of this bit is 0, indicating that the ETM behaves as if the processor is in Secure state at all times.

bit_field_value.name: ETMIDR_SecurityExtensionSupport_0b0
bit_field_value.description: The ETM behaves as if the processor is in Secure state at all times.

bit_field_value.name: ETMIDR_SecurityExtensionSupport_0b1
bit_field_value.description: The ARM architecture Security Extensions are implemented by the processor.

bit_field.name: BranchPacketEncoding
bit_field.description: Branch packet encoding. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that alternative branch packet encoding is implemented.

bit_field_value.name: ETMIDR_BranchPacketEncoding_0b0
bit_field_value.description: The ETM implements the original branch packet encoding.

bit_field_value.name: ETMIDR_BranchPacketEncoding_0b1
bit_field_value.description: The ETM implements the alternative branch packet encoding.

bit_field.name: ImplementorCode
bit_field.description: Implementor code. These bits identify ARM as the implementor of the processor. The value of these bits is 01000001.

bit_field.name: ExtendedExternalInputSelectors
bit_field.description: Extended external input selectors. The value of these bits is 0, indicating that extended external input selectors are not implemented.

bit_field.name: ExtendedExternalInputBus
bit_field.description: Extended external input bus. The value of these bits is 0, indicating that the extended external input bus is not implemented.

bit_field.name: ReadableRegisters
bit_field.description: Readable registers. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that all registers are readable.

bit_field.name: DataAddressComparisons
bit_field.description: Data address comparisons. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that data address comparisons are not supported.

bit_field.name: InstrumentationResources
bit_field.description: Instrumentation resources. The value of these bits is 0b000, indicating that no Instrumentation resources are supported.

bit_field.name: EmbeddedICEwatchpointInputs
bit_field.description: EmbeddedICE watchpoint inputs. The value of these bits is 0b0100, indicating that the number of EmbeddedICE watchpoint inputs implemented is four. These inputs come from the DWT.

bit_field.name: TraceStartStopBlockUsesEmbeddedICEwatchpointInputs
bit_field.description: Trace Start/Stop block uses EmbeddedICE watchpoint inputs. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that the Trace Start/Stop block uses the EmbeddedICE watchpoint inputs.

bit_field.name: EmbeddedICEbehaviorControlImplemented
bit_field.description: EmbeddedICE behavior control implemented. The value of this bit is 0, indicating that the ETMEIBCR is not implemented.

bit_field.name: TimestampingImplemented
bit_field.description: Timestamping implemented. This bit is set to 1, indicating that timestamping is implemented.

bit_field.name: ReducedFunctionCounter
bit_field.description: Reduced function counter. Set to 1 to indicate that Counter 1 is a reduced function counter.

bit_field.name: TimestampEncoding
bit_field.description: Timestamp encoding. Set to 1 to indicate that the timestamp is encoded as a natural binary number.

bit_field.name: TimestampSize
bit_field.description: Timestamp size. Set to 0 to indicate a size of 48 bits.

bit_field.name: StartResourceSelection
bit_field.description: Start resource selection. Setting any of these bits to 1 selects the corresponding EmbeddedICE watchpoint input as a TraceEnable start resource. Bit [0] corresponds to input 1, bit [1] corresponds to input 2, bit [2] corresponds to input 3, and bit [3] corresponds to input 4.

bit_field.name: StopResourceSelection
bit_field.description: Stop resource selection. Setting any of these bits to 1 selects the corresponding EmbeddedICE watchpoint input as a TraceEnable stop resource. Bit [16] corresponds to input 1, bit [17] corresponds to input 2, bit [18] corresponds to input 3, and bit [19] corresponds to input 4.

bit_field.name: TimestampEvent
bit_field.description: Timestamp event.

bit_field.name: TraceID
bit_field.description: Trace ID to output onto the trace bus. On an ETM reset this field is cleared to 0x00.

bit_field.name: ETMpoweredup
bit_field.description: The value of this bit indicates whether you can access the ETM Trace Registers. The value of this bit is always 1, indicating that the ETM Trace Registers can be accessed.

bit_field.name: EXTIN
bit_field.description: A read of these bits returns the value of the EXTIN[1:0] input pins.

bit_field.name: COREHALT
bit_field.description: A read of this bit returns the value of the COREHALT input pin.

bit_field.name: TRIGGER
bit_field.description: A write to this bit sets the TRIGGER output.

register.name: ITATBCTR2
register.description: ETM Integration Test ATB Control 2 Register

bit_field.name: ATREADY
bit_field.description: A read of this bit returns the value of the ETM ATREADY input.

register.name: ITATBCTR0
register.description: ETM Integration Test ATB Control 0 Register

bit_field.name: ATVALID
bit_field.description: A write to this bit sets the value of the ETM ATVALID output.

bit_field.name: Mode
bit_field.description: Enable integration mode. When this bit is set to 1, the device enters integration mode to enable Topology Detection or Integration Testing to be checked. On an ETM reset this bit is cleared to 0.

bit_field.name: CLAIMSET
bit_field.description: A bit programmable register bank which sets the Claim Tag Value. Write 1 to set the bit in the claim tag. A read will return a logic 1 for all implemented locations.

bit_field.name: CLAIMCLR
bit_field.description: A bit programmable register bank that is zero at reset. Write 1 to clear the bit in the claim tag. On reads, returns the current setting of the claim tag.

bit_field.name: WriteAccessCode
bit_field.description: Write Access Code. A write of 0xC5ACCE55 enables further write access to this device. An invalid write will have the affect of removing write access.

bit_field.name: IMP
bit_field.description: Lock mechanism is implemented. This bit always reads 1.

bit_field.name: STATUS
bit_field.description: Lock Status. This bit is HIGH when the device is locked, and LOW when unlocked.

bit_field_value.name: ETMLSR_STATUS_0b1
bit_field_value.description: Write access to the component is blocked. All writes to control registers are ignored. Reads are permitted.

bit_field.name: s8BIT
bit_field.description: Access Lock Register size. This bit reads 0 to indicate a 32-bit register is present.

bit_field.name: NSID
bit_field.description: Reads as b00, Non-secure invasive debug not supported by the ETM.

bit_field.name: NSNID
bit_field.description: Permission for Non-secure non-invasive debug.

bit_field.name: SID
bit_field.description: Reads as b00, Secure invasive debug not supported by the ETM.

bit_field.name: SNID
bit_field.description: Permission for Secure non-invasive debug.

bit_field.name: MajorType
bit_field.description: Major Type and Class

bit_field.name: SubType
bit_field.description: Sub Type

bit_field.name: JEP106
bit_field.description: JEP106 continuation code.

bit_field.name: c4KB
bit_field.description: 4KB Count

bit_field.name: PartNumber
bit_field.description: Part Number [7:0]

bit_field.name: PartNumber
bit_field.description: Part Number [11:8]

bit_field.name: JEP106_identity_code
bit_field.description: JEP106 identity code [3:0]

bit_field.name: JEP106_identity_code
bit_field.description: JEP106 identity code [6:4]

bit_field.name: CustomerModified
bit_field.description: Customer Modified.

bit_field.name: ComponentClass
bit_field.description: Component class

bit_field_value.name: ETMCIDR1_ComponentClass_0b1111
bit_field_value.description: PrimeCell of system component with no standardized register layout, for backward compatibility.
